title: Google\Cloud\ArtifactRegistry\V1beta2\Version
name: Version
description:
The body of a version resource. A version resource represents a collection of components, such as files and other data. This may correspond to a version in many package management schemes.

Generated from protobuf message google.devtools.artifactregistry.v1beta2.Version

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: The name of the version, for example: "projects/p1/locations/us-central1/repositories/repo1/packages/pkg1/versions/art1". If the package or version ID parts contain slashes, the slashes are escaped.

params.name: data.description
params.description: Optional. Description of the version, as specified in its metadata.

params.name: data.create_time
params.description: The time when the version was created.

params.name: data.update_time
params.description: The time when the version was last updated.

params.name: data.related_tags
params.description: Output only. A list of related tags. Will contain up to 100 tags that reference this version.

params.name: data.metadata
params.description: Output only. Repository-specific Metadata stored against this version. The fields returned are defined by the underlying repository-specific resource. Currently, the only resource in use is [DockerImage][google.devtools.artifactregistry.v1.DockerImage]
